<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - TURBOCHARGER - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="10">
            <title>Standard Torque Non-Wastegated Turbocharger</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all protective caps from the turbocharger, pedestal and crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200234" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3303.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger Oil Supply O-Ring and Oil Drain O-Ring</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Crankcase Mounting Pad</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a light coat of grease to a new oil drain O-ring and oil supply O-ring. Install
                    the O-rings into the turbocharger crankcase mounting pad.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200270" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8028a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Right Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware at the Exhaust Manifolds</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1200271" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8028b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Left Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware at the Exhaust Manifolds</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the exhaust pipe assembly to the left and right exhaust manifolds. Finger tighten
                    the mounting hardware.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200235" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3305.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Exhaust Tubes to the Exhaust Manifolds</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the gasket onto the exhaust inlet adapter.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200272" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2630.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Pedestal Rear Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Adapter</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Pedestal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the turbocharger on the mounting pad so the bolt holes in the turbocharger
                    pedestal align with bolt holes in the crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two rear turbocharger pedestal mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to the
                    special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200237" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2633.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Pedestal Front Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Front Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two front turbocharger pedestal mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to the
                    special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200236" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Turbocharger</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Housing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Nuts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Adapter</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two bolts and two nuts that secure the turbocharger to the exhaust inlet
                    adapter. Tighten the bolts to the special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the mounting hardware at the exhaust manifolds to the special torque value.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200238" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3378.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Charge Air Cooling Tube/Crossover Pipe Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Charge Air Cooling Tube/Crossover Pipe Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Intake Manifold Hose</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamp (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate a new compressor outlet seal with clean oil. Install the seal in the
                    turbocharger compressor outlet.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly to the turbocharger
                        compressor housing and air intake hoses.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the four hose clamps (two per side) to secure the hoses to the air intake
                        manifold covers.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">To secure the charge air cooling tube to the turbocharger compressor housing,
                        tighten the turbocharger compressor outlet clamp.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200273" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3377.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="532px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Air Inlet Elbow (Crankcase Breather Elbow)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Air Inlet Elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather Elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather Elbow Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1200274" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="432px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Air Inlet Elbow (Road Draft Tube)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On engines equipped with a crankcase breather elbow</emph>, install the air inlet
                    elbow and the crankcase breather elbow. Tighten the clamps.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On engines equipped with a road draft tube</emph>, install the air inlet elbow.
                    Tighten the clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
